Underneath the bridge, the channel is seperated by a gravel bar. The channel on River-Right is shallow, and slower so it was measured with a Flowtracker.  The channel on River-Left was measured with a tethered boat and ADCP.  Flow tracker measured measured 6.1311 cms in right channel by wading.  ADCP measured 53.73 cms in left channel.   Total Q: 58.8611 cms.  The data collected by bottom tracks is very poor, and it was noticed in the field.  Presummably moving bed is very high.  No moving bed test was collected because the boat track is so poor.  VTG was shown to have the best data. Sources:eHSN v1.2.4

Could only try to do M9 tethered boat mmt. from bridge. Unfortunately, gravel bar in middle seperated the river into two channels (slower and shallow on RB,and deep andfast on LB).  Poor measurement for the shallow channel.  Should probably have used snowshoe crane or or do a difficult wader.  Other channel was a good measurment for GGA/ or VGA, but very poor for BT. Transects for BT were very erratic (77 - 47 cms....) so no loop test performed.    The LB discharge was 14.2 cms, and the RB discharge was 83.7 cms. In total the average flow was 97.9 cms.  2.00 metres above gauge Sources:eHSN v1.2.4
